  "title": "Financial Planning and Analyst",
  "description": "<ul><li>Develop and maintain financial models, forecasts, and scenario analyses to support decision-making. </li><li>Lead the annual budgeting process and periodic forecast updates with strong attention to accuracy and timeliness. </li><li>Perform variance analysis against budget/forecast, delivering actionable insights to management.</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams (sales, engineering, project management) to understand financial drivers and improve forecasting accuracy. </li><li>Track and report on project-level P&L and capital expenditures, ensuring transparency and control. </li><li>Prepare management reports and presentations for headquarters to inform strategic planning. </li><li>Support long-term strategic planning and investment decisions through in-depth financial analysis. </li><li>Analyse cost structures and revenue trends to identify opportunities for efficiency and\ngrowth. </li><li>Assist in ad hoc analysis requests from headquarters</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>HOW TO APPLY:</strong></p><p>Interested applicants, kindly send your resume in MS WORD format or please click on “Apply Now”.</p><p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>Important Note: Trust Recruit Pte Ltd is committed to safeguarding your personal data in accordance with the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA).</p><p>Please read our privacy statement on our corporate website.</p><p>Trust Recruit Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 19C9950</p><p>EA Personnel: Tan Sin Yong (Stella)</p><p>EA Personnel Reg No: R24124127</p>",
